 {"id":"flywheel_gateway-twx","title":"RU: Database Schema Enhancements","description":"## Problem Statement

The Gateway database has placeholder tables for RU (Repo Updater) integration that don't match the actual data structures needed. These need to be completely redesigned to support fleet status, sync operations, and agent-sweep workflows.

## Background

RU (Repo Updater) is a production-grade Bash CLI for managing large collections of GitHub repositories. Key data structures needed:

1. **Fleet Repositories** - All repos being managed
2. **Sync Operations** - Clone/pull history and status
3. **Agent Sweep Sessions** - Multi-phase automated maintenance runs
4. **Agent Sweep Plans** - JSON plans produced by agents
5. **Agent Sweep Executions** - Plan execution results

Current placeholder schema is inadequate:

```typescript
// Existing (insufficient)
export const fleetRepos = sqliteTable("fleet_repos", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),
  name: text("name").notNull(),
  // ... minimal fields
});
```

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Fleet Repositories Table

```typescript
// apps/gateway/src/db/schema.ts

export const fleetRepos = sqliteTable("fleet_repos", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // Repository identification
  owner: text("owner").notNull(),           // GitHub owner/org
  name: text("name").notNull(),             // Repository name
  fullName: text("full_name").notNull(),    // owner/name
  url: text("url").notNull(),               // Clone URL
  sshUrl: text("ssh_url"),                  // SSH URL

  // Local state
  localPath: text("local_path"),            // Where it's cloned
  isCloned: integer("is_cloned", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),

  // Git state
  currentBranch: text("current_branch"),
  defaultBranch: text("default_branch"),
  lastCommit: text("last_commit"),          // SHA
  lastCommitDate: integer("last_commit_date", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  lastCommitAuthor: text("last_commit_author"),

  // Status
  status: text("status").default("unknown"), // healthy|dirty|behind|ahead|diverged|unknown
  hasUncommittedChanges: integer("has_uncommitted_changes", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),
  hasUnpushedCommits: integer("has_unpushed_commits", { mode: "boolean" }).default(false),
  aheadBy: integer("ahead_by").default(0),
  behindBy: integer("behind_by").default(0),

  // Metadata
  description: text("description"),
  language: text("language"),
  stars: integer("stars"),
  isPrivate: integer("is_private", { mode: "boolean" }),
  isArchived: integer("is_archived", { mode: "boolean" }),

  // RU integration
  ruGroup: text("ru_group"),                // Grouping for batch operations
  ruConfig: text("ru_config"),              // JSON config overrides
  agentsmdPath: text("agentsmd_path"),      // Path to AGENTS.md if exists
  lastScanDate: integer("last_scan_date", { mode: "timestamp" }),

  // Timestamps
  addedAt: integer("added_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
  updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  lastSyncAt: integer("last_sync_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
}, (table) => ({
  ownerIdx: index("fleet_repos_owner_idx").on(table.owner),
  statusIdx: index("fleet_repos_status_idx").on(table.status),
  groupIdx: index("fleet_repos_group_idx").on(table.ruGroup),
  fullNameUnique: unique("fleet_repos_full_name_unique").on(table.fullName),
}));
```

### 2. Sync Operations Table

```typescript
export const fleetSyncOps = sqliteTable("fleet_sync_ops", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // Target
  repoId: text("repo_id").references(() => fleetRepos.id),
  repoFullName: text("repo_full_name").notNull(),

  // Operation type
  operation: text("operation").notNull(),   // clone|pull|fetch|push

  // Status
  status: text("status").notNull(),         // pending|running|success|failed|cancelled

  // Results
  startedAt: integer("started_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  completedAt: integer("completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  durationMs: integer("duration_ms"),

  // Git details
  fromCommit: text("from_commit"),          // Before sync
  toCommit: text("to_commit"),              // After sync
  commitCount: integer("commit_count"),     // Number of commits synced
  filesChanged: integer("files_changed"),

  // Error handling
  error: text("error"),
  errorCode: text("error_code"),
  retryCount: integer("retry_count").default(0),

  // Metadata
  triggeredBy: text("triggered_by"),        // user|schedule|agent-sweep
  correlationId: text("correlation_id"),    // For linking related ops

  createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
}, (table) => ({
  repoIdx: index("fleet_sync_ops_repo_idx").on(table.repoId),
  statusIdx: index("fleet_sync_ops_status_idx").on(table.status),
  createdAtIdx: index("fleet_sync_ops_created_at_idx").on(table.createdAt),
}));
```

### 3. Agent Sweep Sessions Table

```typescript
export const agentSweepSessions = sqliteTable("agent_sweep_sessions", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // Scope
  targetRepos: text("target_repos").notNull(),  // JSON array of repo IDs or "*" for all
  repoCount: integer("repo_count").notNull(),

  // Configuration
  config: text("config"),                       // JSON sweep config
  parallelism: integer("parallelism").default(1),

  // Phase tracking
  currentPhase: text("current_phase"),          // phase1_analysis|phase2_planning|phase3_execution
  phase1CompletedAt: integer("phase1_completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  phase2CompletedAt: integer("phase2_completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  phase3CompletedAt: integer("phase3_completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),

  // Status
  status: text("status").notNull(),             // pending|running|paused|completed|failed|cancelled

  // Progress
  reposAnalyzed: integer("repos_analyzed").default(0),
  reposPlanned: integer("repos_planned").default(0),
  reposExecuted: integer("repos_executed").default(0),
  reposFailed: integer("repos_failed").default(0),
  reposSkipped: integer("repos_skipped").default(0),

  // Timing
  startedAt: integer("started_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  completedAt: integer("completed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  totalDurationMs: integer("total_duration_ms"),

  // SLB integration
  slbApprovalRequired: integer("slb_approval_required", { mode: "boolean" }).default(true),
  slbApprovalId: text("slb_approval_id"),
  slbApprovedBy: text("slb_approved_by"),
  slbApprovedAt: integer("slb_approved_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),

  // Metadata
  triggeredBy: text("triggered_by"),
  notes: text("notes"),

  createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
  updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
}, (table) => ({
  statusIdx: index("agent_sweep_sessions_status_idx").on(table.status),
  phaseIdx: index("agent_sweep_sessions_phase_idx").on(table.currentPhase),
  createdAtIdx: index("agent_sweep_sessions_created_at_idx").on(table.createdAt),
}));
```

### 4. Agent Sweep Plans Table

```typescript
export const agentSweepPlans = sqliteTable("agent_sweep_plans", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // References
  sessionId: text("session_id").references(() => agentSweepSessions.id),
  repoId: text("repo_id").references(() => fleetRepos.id),
  repoFullName: text("repo_full_name").notNull(),

  // Plan content (from Phase 2)
  planJson: text("plan_json").notNull(),        // Full JSON plan from agent
  planVersion: integer("plan_version").default(1),

  // Plan summary
  actionCount: integer("action_count"),
  estimatedDurationMs: integer("estimated_duration_ms"),
  riskLevel: text("risk_level"),                // low|medium|high|critical

  // Actions breakdown
  commitActions: integer("commit_actions").default(0),
  releaseActions: integer("release_actions").default(0),
  branchActions: integer("branch_actions").default(0),
  prActions: integer("pr_actions").default(0),
  otherActions: integer("other_actions").default(0),

  // Validation
  validatedAt: integer("validated_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  validationResult: text("validation_result"),  // valid|invalid|warning
  validationErrors: text("validation_errors"),  // JSON array

  // Approval
  approvalStatus: text("approval_status").default("pending"), // pending|approved|rejected|auto_approved
  approvedBy: text("approved_by"),
  approvedAt: integer("approved_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  rejectedReason: text("rejected_reason"),

  // Execution
  executionStatus: text("execution_status"),    // pending|running|completed|failed|skipped
  executedAt: integer("executed_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
  executionResult: text("execution_result"),    // JSON result

  createdAt: integer("created_at", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
  updatedAt: integer("updated_at", { mode: "timestamp" }),
}, (table) => ({
  sessionIdx: index("agent_sweep_plans_session_idx").on(table.sessionId),
  repoIdx: index("agent_sweep_plans_repo_idx").on(table.repoId),
  approvalIdx: index("agent_sweep_plans_approval_idx").on(table.approvalStatus),
}));
```

### 5. Agent Sweep Execution Log Table

```typescript
export const agentSweepLogs = sqliteTable("agent_sweep_logs", {
  id: text("id").primaryKey(),

  // References
  sessionId: text("session_id").references(() => agentSweepSessions.id),
  planId: text("plan_id").references(() => agentSweepPlans.id),
  repoId: text("repo_id").references(() => fleetRepos.id),

  // Log entry
  phase: text("phase").notNull(),               // phase1|phase2|phase3
  level: text("level").notNull(),               // debug|info|warn|error
  message: text("message").notNull(),
  data: text("data"),                           // JSON additional data

  // Timing
  timestamp: integer("timestamp", { mode: "timestamp" }).default(sql`(unixepoch())`),
  durationMs: integer("duration_ms"),

  // Context
  actionType: text("action_type"),              // For phase 3 actions
  actionIndex: integer("action_index"),
}, (table) => ({
  sessionIdx: index("agent_sweep_logs_session_idx").on(table.sessionId),
  timestampIdx: index("agent_sweep_logs_timestamp_idx").on(table.timestamp),
  levelIdx: index("agent_sweep_logs_level_idx").on(table.level),
}));
```

